# Building Intelligent AI Agents - example environment file
#
# Copy this file to `.env` in the repo root and fill in your own keys:
#
#     cp .env.example .env        # Git Bash / Linux / macOS
#
# The labs load it with `load_dotenv(<repo>/.env)`. `.env` is git-ignored -
# never commit your real keys. Check what you have with:
#
#     bash scripts/smoke-test.sh --day 4
#
# No quotes, no spaces around `=`.


# --- Day 4-5 (Modules 7-10): REQUIRED --------------------------------------
# Groq free API - the LLM behind every Day 4 and Day 5 agent lab
# (model: openai/gpt-oss-20b). Get a key: https://console.groq.com/keys
GROQ_API_KEY=gsk_your_groq_key_here


# --- Day 3 (Module 6): required for the external-API labs -------------------
# Serper - Google Search API used by the search tool. https://serper.dev
SERPER_API_KEY=your_serper_key_here

# Wolfram Alpha - compute tool. Create an App at
# https://developer.wolframalpha.com/access to get an AppID.
WOLFRAM_ALPHA_APPID=your_wolfram_appid_here
WOLFRAM_ALPHA_APPNAME=biaa-workshop


# --- Day 2 (Modules 3-4): optional ------------------------------------------
# Hugging Face token. The Day-2 models (distilbert-base-uncased, distilgpt2,
# prajjwal1/bert-tiny, all-MiniLM-L6-v2) are public and download without it;
# set it only if you hit rate limits. https://huggingface.co/settings/tokens
# HF_TOKEN=hf_your_token_here


# --- Optional: BYOK (bring your own key) ------------------------------------
# OpenAI is never required - the labs default to Groq (Day 4-5) and local
# Ollama (Day 3), both free. Set this only if you prefer OpenAI, then
# `pip install openai` (Day-2 text-gen snippet) or `pip install langchain-openai`
# (swap ChatOpenAI for ChatGroq in the agent labs). OpenAI is paid/metered.
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your_openai_key_here


# --- Day 3 (Modules 5-6): no key needed -------------------------------------
# Day 3 runs a LOCAL model via Ollama on http://127.0.0.1:11434 - no API key.
# Pull the model once:  ollama pull llama3.1:8b
